<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2005-02-01.52WS.5" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/801" speakername="Charles Clarke" speakeroffice="The Secretary of State for the Home Department" colnum="52WS"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200405/cmhansrd/cm050201/wmstext/50201m01.htm#50201m01.html_spmin2">
	<p>Following my statement on 12 January, the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) and Association of Chief Police Officers (ACPO) have today published a joint statement entitled &quot;Householders and the use of force against intruders&quot;. This contains a clear explanation of the law and also explains how the police and CPS would handle the investigation and how they would treat the householder. I am placing a copy in the Library of the House.</p>
	<p>The CPS and ACPO will be ensuring this guidance is widely available and the Home Office are wording with them in promulgating it.</p>
</speech>
